BOur%20current%20agreement%20with%20Disney%20has%20approached%20its%20renewal%20date%2C%20and%20we%20will%20not%20agree%20to%20terms%20that%20disadvantage%20our%20members%20while%20benefiting%20Disney's%20own%20live%20TV%20products%2C%26quot%3B%20YouTube%20TV%20said%20in%20an%20email%20to%20subscribers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDespite%20our%20best%20efforts%2C%20we%20have%20not%20been%20able%20to%20reach%20a%20fair%20deal%2C%20and%20starting%20today%2C%20October%2030%2C%202025%2C%20Disney%20programming%20will%20not%20be%20available%20on%20YouTube%20TV%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20shared%20on%20its%20blog%2C%20YouTube%20said%20Disney%20%26quot%3Bused%20the%20threat%20of%20a%20blackout%20on%20YouTube%20TV%20as%20a%20negotiating%20tactic%20to%20force%20deal%20terms%20that%20would%20raise%20prices%20on%20our%20customers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20decision%20directly%20harms%20our%20subscribers%20while%20benefiting%20their%20own%20live%20TV%20products%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Disney%20spokesperson%20said%20that%20Google%2C%20YouTube's%20parent%20company%2C%20had%20refused%20to%20pay%20fair%20rates%20for%20its%20channels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20a%20%243%20trillion%20market%20cap%2C%20Google%20is%20using%20its%20market%20dominance%20to%20eliminate%20competition%20and%20undercut%20the%20industry-standard%20terms%20we've%20successfully%20negotiated%20with%20every%20other%20distributor%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Disney%20spokesperson%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYouTube%20TV%20said%20in%20its%20email%20to%20customers%20that%20it%20was%20working%20to%20bring%20Disney%20content%20back%20to%20the%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20committed%20to%20continuing%20to%20work%20with%20Disney%20to%20reach%20an%20agreement%2C%20but%20if%20their%20content%20is%20unavailable%20for%20an%20extended%20period%20of%20time%2C%20we'll%20offer%20our%20subscribers%20a%20%2420%20credit.%26quot%3B%20It%20did%20not%20specify%20how%20long%20it%20would%20consider%20an%20extended%20period%20of%20time%20to%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDisputes%20about%20carriage%20and%20distribution%20deals%20aren't%20uncommon%20in%20the%20broadcasting%20industry%2C%20and%20have%20often%20resulted%20in%20short-term%20blackouts.%20In%202023%2C%20Disney%20was%20locked%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcharter-thinks-cable-tv-sucks-now-disney-dispute-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eugly%20dispute%20with%20Charter%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20resulted%20in%20channels%20like%20ESPN%20briefly%20being%20taken%20off%20the%20air%20for%20the%20cable%20company's%20millions%20of%20subscribers.%20In%202024%2C%20Disney%20yanked%20its%20networks%20from%20DirecTV%20for%20a%20two-week%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYouTube%20also%20had%20tense%20carriage%20negotiations%20with%20the%20likes%20of%20NBCUniversal%20and%20Fox%20in%20recent%20months%2C%20though%20deals%20were%20reached%20before%20channels%20went%20dark.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYouTube%20has%20become%20a%20powerful%20force%20in%20TV%2C%20giving%20it%20significant%20leverage%20in%20such%20talks.%20YouTube%20is%20the%20top%20media%20distributor%20in%20the%20US%2C%20capturing%2012.6%25%20of%20watch-time%20in%20September%2C%20according%20to%20Nielsen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYouTube%20TV%2C%20its%20cable-like%20offering%20that%20costs%20%2482.99%20a%20month%20in%20the%20US%2C%20had%20%26quot%3Bmore%20than%208%20million%20subscribers%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20an%20October%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaolo%20Pescatore%2C%20an%20independent%20tech%20and%20media%20analyst%2C%20predicts%20further%20carriage%20disputes%20involving%20YouTube%2C%20Disney%2C%20and%20other%20companies%20as%20they%20battle%20to%20own%20the%20subscriber%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20so%20much%20at%20stake%2C%26quot%3B%20Pescatore%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20In%20this%20particular%20skirmish%2C%20Pescatore%20added%2C%20