%20focused%20on%20perfection.%20He%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20problems%20here%20we%20have%20is%20that%20the%20better%20is%20the%20enemy%20of%20good%3A%20It%20has%20to%20be%20perfect.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20NATO%20should%20be%20learning%20from%20Ukraine%2C%20which%20will%20proceed%20with%20equipment%20rated%20%26quot%3Bsix%20to%20seven%26quot%3B%20out%20of%2010%2C%20while%20Western%20militaries%20insist%20on%20reaching%20%26quot%3Bnine%20or%2010.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20a%20problem%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20building%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-companies-making-cheaper-missiles-conflict-like-war-with-china-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eaffordable%20mass%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20Western%20industry%20figures%20have%20highlighted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESteve%20Milano%2C%20senior%20director%20of%20advanced%20effects%20at%20Anduril%2C%20said%20in%20a%20recent%20Cogs%20of%20War%20podcast%20that%20%26quot%3Bwe've%20got%20the%20exquisite%20weapons%20systems%2C%20but%20we%20really%20need%20affordable%2C%20sufficient%20mass.%26quot%3B%20His%20company%20is%20among%20several%20working%20toward%20cheaper%20missiles%20that%20give%20the%20US%20the%20ability%20to%20stockpile%20for%20a%20high-intensity%20fight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20has%20been%20eye-opening%20in%20this%20respect.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EUkraine's%20defense%20industry%20is%20booming%2C%20with%20both%20small%2C%20homegrown%20companies%20and%20large%20ones%20quickly%20innovating%20and%20producing.%20It's%20fighting%20to%20survive%2C%20a%20position%20NATO%20countries%20are%20not%20in%2C%20but%20many%20of%20them%20say%20they%20must%20learn%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feurope-weapon-making-issue-highlighted-ukraine-being-faster-denmark-pm-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehow%20Ukraine%20is%20innovating%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20building%20so%20quickly%2C%20lessons%20the%20alliance%20would%20need%20in%20a%20hard%20fight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223f840a6f-9e5f-466c-b511-e1017bd3f730%5C%22%3ECheaper%20weapons%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Patriot%20air%20defense%20system%20on%20tarmac%20with%20a%20cloudy%20skiy%20behind%20it%20and%20people%20standing%20beside%20it%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6900995c0be9845f2dc53621%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Patriot%20system%20is%20great%20for%20stopping%20missiles%2C%20but%20is%20a%20bad%20cost-per-return%20if%20used%20against%20cheap%20targets%20like%20drones.%3Cp%3EDominika%20Zarzycka%2FNurPhoto%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDrones%20are%20a%20driving%20factor%20in%20such%20considerations.%20Inexpensive%20drones%20have%20destroyed%20expensive%20tanks%2C%20sunk%20costly%20warships%2C%20and%20stressed%20top%20air%20defense%20systems.%20Cheap%20mass%20is%20straining%20the%20exquisite.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20air%20defense%20fight%2C%20Ukraine%20continues%20leaning%20into%20drones%20for%20precision%20strikes%20on%20a%20budget%20while%20also%20developing%20cheap%20interceptor%20systems%20to%20take%20out%20enemy%20threats.%20And%20NATO%20is%20paying%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKipurs'%20products%20are%20not%20exactly%20the%20minimum%20viable%20product.%20They%20are%20advanced%20and%20use%20AI%20as%20part%20of%20their%20modern%20systems%2C%20but%20they%20are%20far%20from%20the%20expensive%20surface-to-air%20missiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20on%20the%20back%20of%20a%20truck%20shoots%20a%20gun%20into%20the%20air%2C%20with%20another%20man%20in%20the%20front%20of%20the%20truck%20and%20another%20standing%20beside%20it%2C%20all%20wearing%20camouflage%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69009a93c007ca8c2737be90%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20soldiers%20use%20low-cost%20solutions%20to%20stop%20Russian%20drones.%3Cp%3EOxana%20Chorna%2FGlobal%20Images%20Ukraine%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20with%20air%20defense%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20need%20a%20multitude%20of%20tools%26quot%3B%20to%20meet%20a%20range%20of%20threats%2C%20and%20you%20probably%20want%20a%2010%3A1%20ratio%20between%20the%20cost%20of%20the%20interceptor%20and%20the%20average%20cost%20of%20a%20target.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKipurs%20said%20that%20it's%20not%20that%20the%20West%20doesn't%20need%20advanced%20technology%2C%20but%20it's%20about%20balance.%20Ukraine%20still%20wants%20Patriots%2C%20but%20it%20is%20also%20pouring%20money%20into%20far%20cheaper%20alternatives%20able%20to%20be%20produced%20at%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228a4ea746-d1ec-471f-9745-ac12fcdb6b30%5C%22%3EA%20change%20for%20the%20West%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20West%20is%20nervously%20watching%20Ukraine%2C%20worried%20Russia%20may%20attack%20elsewhere%20in%20Europe.%20That%20war%20likely%20would%20not%20look%20the%20same%20as%20Ukraine.%20NATO%20militaries%20are%20far%20larger%2C%20with%20much%20more%20advanced%20weaponry%2C%20meaning%20they%20would%20rely%20less%20on%20cheaper%20systems%20Ukraine%20needs%2C%20like%20drones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20affordable%20mass%20and%20deep%20magazines%20cannot%20be%20shrugged%20off%20as%20unnecessary.%20This%20war%20has%20been%20a%20clear%20wake-up%20call%20for%20Western%20militaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDanish%20Defense%20Minister%20Troels%20Lund%20Poulsen%20told%20Business%20Insider%20earlier%20this%20year%20that%20the%20West%20needs%20significantly%20more%20inexpensive%20weaponry%20to%20meet%20the%20threats%20posed%20by%20Russia%20and%20China%2C%20calling%20this%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20lessons%26quot%3B%20from%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGabrielius%20Landsbergis%2C%20Lithuania's%20former%20foreign%20minister%2C%20previously%2