-bubble-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estock%20market%20bubble%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20if%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20is%20set%20to%20continue%20slashing%20rates%2C%20one%20might%20be%20tempted%20to%20ask%3A%20so%20what%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20even%20with%20valuations%20elevated%2C%20the%20old%20maxim%20of%20%26quot%3Bdon't%20fight%20the%20Fed%26quot%3B%20may%20prove%20to%20be%20prudent%20advice%20in%20the%20near%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20interest%20rates%20fall%2C%20investors%20are%20encouraged%20to%20move%20out%20of%20short-term%20assets%20like%20Treasury%20bills%20and%20certificates%20of%20deposit%20to%20find%20yield%20elsewhere.%20Often%2C%20that's%20in%20stocks.%20Historically%2C%20investors%20have%20justified%20higher%20stock%20valuations%20when%20interest%20rates%20have%20been%20low.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELower%20rates%20also%20help%20support%20economic%20growth%20and%20the%20job%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20definitely%20not%20fight%20the%20Fed%20in%20this%20case%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Katie%20Klingensmith%2C%20the%20chief%20investment%20strategist%20at%20Edelman%20Financial%20Engines.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20Fed%20is%20pretty%20clearly%20now%20concerned%20around%20not%20necessarily%20asset%20prices%20%E2%80%94%20financial%20asset%20prices%2C%20the%20stock%20market%20%E2%80%94%20but%20they're%20pretty%20clearly%20concerned%20around%20downside%20risk%20to%20the%20labor%20market%20and%20to%20the%20broader%20economy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJeff%20DeGraaf%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20chairman%20of%20Renaissance%20Macro%20Research%2C%20echoed%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20thing%20that%20gets%20overlooked%20is%20that%20you've%20got%20a%20Fed%20starting%20an%20easing%20cycle%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20about%20bubble%20concerns.%20%26quot%3BTraditionally%2C%20you%20don't%20burst%20bubbles%20in%20an%20easing%20cycle%3B%20you%20burst%20them%20in%20a%20tightening%20cycle.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecent%20data%20